heart shaped donuts ❤️🍩 tryna be as smooth as I can Never knew I needed a heart shaped mold so badly🫣 it would be even better if my heart on my latte Art didn’t look like an onion instead 😮‍💨 lmk what u guys think in the comments✨ . Recipe Donut Dough Serving size - 6 heart shaped donuts Yeast mixture - 3/4 cups milk - 2 tsp instant yeast - 3 tbsp sugar Mix together and let it rise Flour mix - 2 cups flour - 1/2 tsp salt Mix it with the yeast mixture and add in 20g of butter *you can mix the wet and dry ingredients together without letting the yeast rise first as well Knead for twenty minutes and let it double in size ( takes about an hour ) Take it out and using the heart shaped mold cut out around 6 pieces and let it double in size before frying in medium heat for around 3 mins before flipping. Let the donuts cool before coating it with Sugar and enjoy✨ . What a perfect breakfast looks like ! Palappam, paneer roast and coconut milk. Recipe for palappam: (This is slightly different from the usual recipe because I've not used soda and yeast) 1. Soak one cup raw rice and one cup idli rice for 6 hrs. Separately soak 6 tbsp urad dal and 1 tsp fenugreek for 6 hrs. 2. To a mixer, add the dal, fenugreek and a handful of coconut. Add lil water and blend it into a smooth thin batter. Then add the rice and blend the batter all together by adding water and salt. 3. Let it ferment for 8-10 hrs. You can make regular hoppers or flat griddle dosas. Recipe for coconut milk: 1. Add 1 cardamom, 3 tbsp sugar and one cup chopped coconut to a mixer. 2. Grind it and then add 3/4 cup water to extract the thick coconut milk. Done! Enjoy! ❤ . . .
